The spiritual leader of the Brotherhood of the Cross and Star, Leader Olumba Olumba Obu, has handed over to his son, His Holiness Olumba Olumba Obu. The spokesperson of the Kingdom, Christ Shepherd Edet Archibong, disclosed this in a press conference in Calabar, Cross River State capital. He said that the founder of the Kingdom has handed over the Kingdom to his son, His Holiness Olumba Olumba Obu. “Leader Obu had finished His work of administering the Kingdom. He no more makes public appearances because everything is now done by His son, His Holiness Olumba Olumba Obu in fulfillment of the prophecy. “Leader Olumba Olumba Obu’s absence from the public scene has led to the insinuation in some quarters that He is dead. “The ancient of days is above death and never dies. He is alive and existing in the dual nature of spirit and human,” the Shepherd Archibong disclosed. He said Brotherhood of the Cross and Star is neither a Church nor a religion nor a family enterprise but the Kingdom of God on earth, created by God where the Children of God coexist in love and righteousness, devoid of barriers of race, religion social status and agenda The spokesperson listed the business empire of the group to include printing press, royal farms, rubber plantation, palm plantation, bakery and table Water. The spokesperson, however, announced the 2020 anniversary of the coronation of the King of Kings and Lord of Lords, His Holiness Olumba Olumba Obu scheduled to hold on August 9, 2020.